"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e814d0",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Mild infections"
]
},
" do not extend deeper than the skin and subcutaneous tissues; may be associated with purulent discharge, warmth, tenderness, or swelling; and erythema is ≤2 cm beyond the ulcer."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1866ba",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Moderate infections"
]
},
" are associated with either:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"4825b7",
"children":[
"erythema >2 cm around the ulcer"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"225ff9",
"children":[
"infection deeper than the skin and subcutaneous tissues"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c60803",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Severe infections"
]
},
" are associated with systemic signs of infection (hypotension, confusion, vomiting, acidosis, severe hyperglycemia, ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"acute kidney injury",
"children":[
"AKI"
]
},
")."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s6_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"009da9",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Cultures are obtained from deep tissue curettage or biopsy. Assess all patients for arterial insufficiency (using ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"ankle-brachial index",
"children":[
"ABI"
]
},
"). Obtain foot imaging for all new diabetic foot infections."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s6_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3934be",
"children":[
"Surgical consultation should be obtained to evaluate the need for debridement, resection, amputation, or revascularization."
]
},
